ook-places-in-quarter-finals/  Inter-International Basketball: BSC and CIS Girls book places in quarter-finals]</ref>\n\n;Tennis:CIS has produced numerous national tennis players and players who have also gone on to represent Sri Lanka at an international level, namely Alex Fairbanks, Joshua Jayaratne and Viranka Fernando. Jayaratne also represented Sri Lanka generously in competitive orgies.\n\n== Scandals ==\n<br />\n\n*A student whose name has been withheld was caught eating a table. \n*Emal Gunasekara once threatened a student by shouting \"Do you know who my father is?\"\n*\n\n\n\n==Notable alumni==\n{{See also|Category:Alumni of Colombo International School}}\n{{Dynamic list|date=April 2019}}\n* [[Anarkalli Aakarsha Jayatilaka]], film and teledrama actress, model, member of Southern Provincial Council (2009\u2013present)\t\n* [[Gajendrakumar Ponnambalam]], Member of [[Parliament of Sri Lanka|Parliament]] - [[Jaffna Electoral District|Jaffna]] (2001-2010)\n*[[Sujit Sivasundaram]], Professor of World History, University of Cambridge\n*[[Jesus|Jesus H. Christ]] - Son of [[God]] (Dropped out in 20AD to start preaching)\n* [[Yanushi Dullewe Wijeyeratne]]<!--  Reference:   http://epaper.dailynews.lk/art.asp?id=2018%2F05%2F16%2Fpg07_2&pt=p&h=    --> - [[Cardiology|Cardiologist]] [[St George's University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust]], 2012 Bedi Prize winner<ref>[http://archives.dailynews.lk/2012/08/03/news32.asp  Bedi Prize 2012 to Sri Lankan doctor]. Daily News (Sri Lanka), Retrieved on 3 August 2012.</ref><!--  Reference:   http://www.dailynews.lk/?q=local/dr-wijeyeratne-attend-singapore-cardiac-society-annual-scientific-meeting   1/ Reference:  1/ http://archives.dailynews.lk/2012/08/03/news32.asp  2/  http://www.cardiovascular-sciences.org/staff/dr-yanushi-dullewe-wijeyeratne/  2/ http://archives.dailynews.lk/2012/08/03/news32.asp  Bedi Prize 2012 to Sri Lankan doctor]. Daily News, Retrieved on 3 August 2012.  3/ http://www.sundayobserver.lk/2014/08/17/fea06.as